## Key Patterns

### Services layer (`services/`)
- Business logic, no HTTP concerns
- Can call Supabase, Stripe, external APIs
- Fire-and-forget pattern for non-critical ops (emails, analytics)

### API routes (`app/api/`)
- Input validation with Zod
- Consistent error responses: `{ error: string, code?: string }`
- Rate limiting via Upstash (when configured)

### Env detection
- `RESEND_API_KEY` presence → Resend, else SMTP/Mailpit
- `BNESIM_API_KEY` presence → live eSIM, else mock
- Stripe Proxy → defers init to runtime

